{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778903945115,"sessionID":"ses_1d1105b2dffeoypsZAOjVXoVJo","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"functions.read:19","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/src/ontology/uberon.Makefile"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/src/ontology/uberon.Makefile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ## Customize Makefile settings for uberon\n2: ##\n3: ## If you need to customize your Makefile, make\n4: ## changes here rather than in the main Makefile\n5: \n6: BRIDGEDIR =            bridge\n7: CONFIGDIR =            config\n8: TAXMODSDIR =           taxmods\n9: BRI=                   true\n10: \n11: OWLSRC =               $(TMPDIR)/uberon-edit.owl\n12: POSTPROCESS_SRC =      $(TMPDIR)/uberon.owl\n13: CATALOG_DYNAMIC =      catalog-dynamic.xml\n14: OWLTOOLS_NO_CAT=       OWLTOOLS_MEMORY=$(OWLTOOLS_MEMORY) owltools\n15: OWLTOOLS_CAT_DYNAMIC=  OWLTOOLS_MEMORY=$(OWLTOOLS_MEMORY) owltools --catalog-xml $(CATALOG_DYNAMIC)\n16: \n17: \n18: DC =                   http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1\n19: RELEASE =              $(URIBASE)/uberon/releases/$(TODAY)\n20: QELK =                 --silence-elk\n21: PART_OF =              BFO_0000050\n22: \n23: \n24: all: uberon-qc\n25: \techo \"make $@ succeeded...\"\n26: \n27: \n28: # Enable second expansion of prerequisites (GNU Make only!).\n29: # We need this to expand the COLLECTED_*_SOURCES variables in the\n30: # composite pipeline.\n31: .SECONDEXPANSION:\n32: \n33: \n34: # ----------------------------------------\n35: # XML CATALOG\n36: # ----------------------------------------\n37: \n38: $(CATALOG_DYNAMIC):\n39: \t@echo \"From this day (12 March 2021) forward, $(CATALOG_DYNAMIC) is maintained\"\n40: \t@echo \"manually. If you must update it, run 'make update_dynamic_catalog'.\"\n41: \t@echo \"Please review the diff carefully as some entries may be omitted.\"\n42: \n43: .PHONY: update_dynamic_catalog\n44: update_dynamic_catalog:\n45: \t@echo \"WARNING: You are updating the dynamic catalog. Note that this is done on\"\n46: \t@echo \"WARNING: the basis of a previous run of WARNING: the pipeline, so all\"\n47: \t@echo \"WARNING: files are expected to be available. Do not do this if you dont\"\n48: \t@echo \"WARNING: know what you are doing.\"\n49: \t$(SCRIPTSDIR)/make-catalog.pl uberon.owl mirror/ncbitaxon.owl imports/*_import.owl \\\n50: \t\tmirror/ro.owl imports/local-*owl $(BRIDGEDIR)/*owl > $@.tmp && \\\n51: \t\tmv $@.tmp $@\n52: \n53: \n54: # ----------------------------------------\n55: # TESTS/QC\n56: # ----------------------------------------\n57: # This section defines the composition of the test suites (i.e., which\n58: # checks are performed). The checks themselves are defined elsewhere in\n59: # this Makefile (mostly in the REPORTS section further below).\n60: \n61: # This target is invoked as part of the automated CI workflow.\n62: # To include a specific check/report in the CI workflow, add it\n63: # to the pre-requisites here.\n64: test: $(REPORTDIR)/uberon-basic-allcycles \\\n65: \t$(REPORTDIR)/bfo-check.txt \\\n66: \t$(REPORTDIR)/taxon-constraint-check.txt \\\n67: \t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon-edit-xp-check \\\n68: \tobocheck \\\n69: \ttest_obo_serialisation \\\n70: \ttest_obsolete \\\n71: \ttest_owlaxioms\n72: \n73: # The other targets are manually triggered.\n74: # 'checks' is a subset of 'uberon-qc'.\n75: checks: $(REPORTDIR)/bfo-check.txt \\\n76: \t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon-edit-obscheck.txt \\\n77: \t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon-edit-xp-check \\\n78: \t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon-obscheck.txt \\\n79: \t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon-orphans \\\n80: \t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon.obo-OWL-check\n81: \n82: uberon-qc: checks \\\n83: \tquick-bridge-checks \\\n84: \tbridge-checks \\\n85: \textra-full-bridge-checks \\\n86: \t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon-basic-allcycles \\\n87: \t$(REPORTDIR)/basic-orphans \\\n88: \t$(REPORTDIR)/composite-metazoan-dv.txt \\\n89: \t$(REPORTDIR)/taxon-constraint-check.txt \\\n90: \t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon-dv.txt \\\n91: \t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon-orphans \\\n92: \t$(REPORTDIR)/stages\n93: \tcat $(REPORTDIR)/uberon-orphans \\\n94: \t\t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon-edit-obscheck.txt \\\n95: \t\t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon-edit-xp-check \\\n96: \t\t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon-orphans \\\n97: \t\t$(REPORTDIR)/uberon-dv.txt \\\n98: \t\t$(REPORTDIR)/composite-metazoan-dv.txt\n99: \n100: quick-qc: $(REPORTDIR)/uberon-edit-obscheck.txt\n101: \tcat $(REPORTDIR)/uberon-edit-obscheck.txt\n102: \n103: .PHONY: checks uberon-qc quick-qc\n104: \n105: \n106: # ----------------------------------------\n107: # BUILDING UBERON ITSELF\n108: # ----------------------------------------\n109: \n110: # Step 1: Preprocessing. We Merge the edit file file with imports and\n111: # list of contributors, then expand macros (except RO:0002175, which\n112: # only needs to be expanded for QC purposes).\n113: $(OWLSRC): $(SRC) $(REPORTDIR)/$(SRC)-gocheck $(REPORTDIR)/$(SRC)-iconv\n114: \t@echo \"STRONG WARNING: issues/contributor.owl needs to be manually updated.\"\n115: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< -i issues/contributor.owl \\\n116: \t\t expand --no-expand-term http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002175 \\\n117: \t\t\t-o $@\n118: \n119: # Step 2: Reasoning.\n120: # For the temporary injection of property chains, see\n121: # <https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/2381>\n122: DEVELOPS_FROM_CHAIN=$(COMPONENTSDIR)/develops-from-chains.owl\n123: # The 'materialize' step is too resource-intensive for the GitHub\n124: # Action runners, so we leave it out when running online QC checks, see\n125: # <https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/pull/3087#issuecomment-1755553647>\n126: ifeq ($(GH_ACTION),true)\n127: MATERIALIZE=\n128: else\n129: MATERIALIZE = materialize -T $(CONFIGDIR)/basic_properties.txt -r elk\n130: endif\n131: $(POSTPROCESS_SRC): $(OWLSRC) $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-bfo.owl $(DEVELOPS_FROM_CHAIN)\n132: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $(OWLSRC) -i $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-bfo.owl \\\n133: \t               -i $(DEVELOPS_FROM_CHAIN) \\\n134: \t         relax $(MATERIALIZE) \\\n135: \t         reason -r elk --exclude-duplicate-axioms true \\\n136: \t                       --equivalent-classes-allowed asserted-only \\\n137: \t         unmerge -i $(DEVELOPS_FROM_CHAIN) \\\n138: \t         annotate -O $(URIBASE)/uberon.owl -V $(RELEASE)/uberon.owl -o $@\n139: \n140: # Step 3: Postprocessing. We merge some files that are derived from the\n141: # previous step.\n142: POSTPROCESS_ADDITIONS = subsets/human-tags.ofn \\\n143: \t\t\tsubsets/mouse-tags.ofn\n144: uberon.owl: $(POSTPROCESS_SRC) $(POSTPROCESS_ADDITIONS)\n145: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< $(foreach add,$(POSTPROCESS_ADDITIONS),-i $(add)) -o $@\n146: \n147: \n148: # ----------------------------------------\n149: # MIRRORS\n150: # ----------------------------------------\n151: \n152: # All the following mirrors are needed, not for imports, but for\n153: # Uberon-specific pipelines (especially the composite-* stuff).\n154: # That's why they are not handled by the ODK-generated Makefile.\n155: \n156: ## ONTOLOGY: allen-dhba\n157: .PHONY: mirror-allen-dhba\n158: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-dhba.owl\n159: mirror-allen-dhba: | $(TMPDIR)\n160: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L https://github.com/brain-bican/developing_human_brain_atlas_ontology/raw/main/dhbao-base.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-dhba-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 && \\\n161: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-dhba-download.owl -o $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl ; fi\n162: \n163: ## ONTOLOGY: allen-dmba\n164: .PHONY: mirror-allen-dmba\n165: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-dmba.owl\n166: mirror-allen-dmba: | $(TMPDIR)\n167: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L https://github.com/brain-bican/developing_mouse_brain_atlas_ontology/raw/main/dmbao-base.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-dmba-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 && \\\n168: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-dmba-download.owl -o $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl ; fi\n169: \n170: ## ONTOLOGY: allen-hba\n171: .PHONY: mirror-allen-hba\n172: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-hba.owl\n173: mirror-allen-hba: | $(TMPDIR)\n174: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L https://github.com/brain-bican/human_brain_atlas_ontology/raw/main/hbao-base.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-hba-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 && \\\n175: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-hba-download.owl -o $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl ; fi\n176: \n177: ## ONTOLOGY: allen-mba\n178: .PHONY: mirror-allen-mba\n179: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-mba.owl\n180: mirror-allen-mba: | $(TMPDIR)\n181: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L https://github.com/brain-bican/mouse_brain_atlas_ontology/raw/main/mbao-base.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-mba-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 && \\\n182: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-mba-download.owl -o $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl ; fi\n183: \n184: ## ONTOLOGY: allen-pba\n185: .PHONY: mirror-allen-pba\n186: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-pba.owl\n187: mirror-allen-pba: | $(TMPDIR)\n188: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L https://github.com/brain-bican/primate_brain_atlas_ontology/raw/main/pbao-base.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-pba-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 && \\\n189: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/allen-pba-download.owl -o $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl ; fi\n190: \n191: ## ONTOLOGY: ceph\n192: .PHONY: mirror-ceph\n193: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/ceph.owl\n194: mirror-ceph: | $(TMPDIR)\n195: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L $(URIBASE)/ceph.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/ceph-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 &&\\\n196: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/ceph-download.owl -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n197: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n198: \n199: ## ONTOLOGY: cteno\n200: .PHONY: mirror-cteno\n201: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/cteno.owl\n202: mirror-cteno: | $(TMPDIR)\n203: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L $(URIBASE)/cteno.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/cteno-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 &&\\\n204: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/cteno-download.owl -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n205: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n206: \n207: ## ONTOLOGY: ehdaa2\n208: .PHONY: mirror-ehdaa2\n209: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/ehdaa2.owl\n210: mirror-ehdaa2: | $(TMPDIR)\n211: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then $(ROBOT) convert -I https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cmungall/human-developmental-anatomy-ontology/uberon/src/ontology/ehdaa2-edit.obo -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n212: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n213: \n214: ## ONTOLOGY: emapa\n215: .PHONY: mirror-emapa\n216: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/emapa.owl\n217: mirror-emapa: | $(TMPDIR)\n218: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L $(URIBASE)/emapa.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/emapa-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 &&\\\n219: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/emapa-download.owl -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n220: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n221: \n222: ## ONTOLOGY: fbbt\n223: .PHONY: mirror-fbbt\n224: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/fbbt.owl\n225: mirror-fbbt: | $(TMPDIR)\n226: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L $(URIBASE)/fbbt.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/fbbt-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 &&\\\n227: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/fbbt-download.owl -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n228: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n229: \n230: ## ONTOLOGY: fbdv\n231: .PHONY: mirror-fbdv\n232: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/fbdv.owl\n233: mirror-fbdv: | $(TMPDIR)\n234: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L $(URIBASE)/fbdv.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/fbdv-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 &&\\\n235: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/fbdv-download.owl -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n236: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n237: \n238: ## ONTOLOGY: ma\n239: .PHONY: mirror-ma\n240: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/ma.owl\n241: mirror-ma: | $(TMPDIR)\n242: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L $(URIBASE)/ma.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/ma-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 &&\\\n243: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/ma-download.owl -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n244: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n245: \n246: ## ONTOLOGY: poro\n247: .PHONY: mirror-poro\n248: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/poro.owl\n249: mirror-poro: | $(TMPDIR)\n250: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L $(URIBASE)/poro.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/poro-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 &&\\\n251: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/poro-download.owl -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n252: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n253: \n254: ## ONTOLOGY: wbbt\n255: .PHONY: mirror-wbbt\n256: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/wbbt.owl\n257: mirror-wbbt: | $(TMPDIR)\n258: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L $(URIBASE)/wbbt.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/wbbt-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 &&\\\n259: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/wbbt-download.owl -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n260: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n261: \n262: ## ONTOLOGY: wbls\n263: .PHONY: mirror-wbls\n264: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/wbls.owl\n265: mirror-wbls: | $(TMPDIR)\n266: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L $(URIBASE)/wbls.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/wbls-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 &&\\\n267: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/wbls-download.owl -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n268: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n269: \n270: ## ONTOLOGY: xao\n271: .PHONY: mirror-xao\n272: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/xao.owl\n273: mirror-xao: | $(TMPDIR)\n274: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L $(URIBASE)/xao.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/xao-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 &&\\\n275: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/xao-download.owl -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n276: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n277: \n278: ## ONTOLOGY: zfa\n279: .PHONY: mirror-zfa\n280: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/zfa.owl\n281: mirror-zfa: | $(TMPDIR)\n282: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L $(URIBASE)/zfa.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/zfa-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 &&\\\n283: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/zfa-download.owl -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n284: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n285: \n286: ## ONTOLOGY: caro\n287: .PHONY: mirror-caro\n288: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/caro.owl\n289: mirror-caro: | $(TMPDIR)\n290: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L $(URIBASE)/caro.owl --create-dirs -o $(MIRRORDIR)/caro-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 &&\\\n291: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(MIRRORDIR)/caro-download.owl -o $@.tmp.owl &&\\\n292: \t\tmv $@.tmp.owl $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n293: \n294: ## ONTOLOGY: sslso\n295: .PHONY: mirror-sslso\n296: .PRECIOUS: $(MIRRORDIR)/life-sslso.owl\n297: mirror-sslso: | $(TMPDIR)\n298: \tif [ $(MIR) = true ] && [ $(IMP) = true ]; then curl -L https://github.com/obophenotype/developmental-stage-ontologies/releases/latest/download/life-stages-base.owl --create-dirs -o $(TMPDIR)/life-stages-download.owl --retry 4 --max-time 200 && \\\n299: \t\t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(TMPDIR)/life-stages-download.owl -o $(TMPDIR)/$@.owl; fi\n300: \n301: \n302: # ----------------------------------------\n303: # \"LOCAL\" IMPORTS\n304: # ----------------------------------------\n305: ifeq ($(strip $(IMP)),true)\n306: \n307: # The following imports are used in Uberon-specific pipelines. They are\n308: # *not* updated as part of the refresh-imports pipeline. In fact, they\n309: # are normally never updated automatically, since Uberon-specific\n310: # pipelines are typically run with IMP set to false.\n311: \n312: # By default, we would like to simply use the mirrored ontology as it\n313: # is, but to avoid injecting random crap, we make a pseudo-base.\n314: .PRECIOUS: imports/local-%.owl\n315: imports/local-%.owl: mirror/%.owl\n316: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< \\\n317: \t\t        --base-iri $(URIBASE)/$(shell echo $* | tr [a-z] [A-Z]) \\\n318: \t\t        --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false \\\n319: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n320: \n321: # We need a special case for FBbt/dv because of the mixed-case prefix\n322: imports/local-fb%.owl: mirror/fb%.owl\n323: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< --base-iri $(URIBASE)/FB \\\n324: \t\t        --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false \\\n325: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n326: \n327: # Ditto for WBbt/ls\n328: imports/local-wb%.owl: mirror/wb%.owl\n329: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< --base-iri $(URIBASE)/WB \\\n330: \t\t        --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false \\\n331: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n332: \n333: # For EHDAA2, we need to preserve the AEO classes as well\n334: imports/local-ehdaa2.owl: mirror/ehdaa2.owl\n335: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< \\\n336: \t\t        --base-iri $(URIBASE)/EHDAA2_ --base-iri $(URIBASE)/AEO_ \\\n337: \t\t        --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false \\\n338: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n339: \n340: # Allen ontologies\n341: imports/local-allen-%.owl: mirror/allen-%.owl\n342: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< \\\n343: \t\t        --base-iri https://purl.brain-bican.org/ontology/$*o/$(shell echo $* | tr [a-z] [A-Z])_ \\\n344: \t\t        --axioms external --preserve-structure false --trim false \\\n345: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n346: \n347: # For the life stages ontology, we already got a base from upstream, but\n348: # we can't use the generic rule above as the ontology contains (by\n349: # construction) classes from all over the place. So we just convert it\n350: # to OFN without removing anything.\n351: imports/local-sslso.owl: mirror/sslso.owl\n352: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< -f ofn -o $@\n353: \n354: # For the following ontologies, in addition to removing axioms about\n355: # external entities we also need to replace some old-style properties.\n356: # ----------------------------------------\n357: # EMAPA also needs translation between TS-style stages to MmusDv stages\n358: imports/local-emapa.owl: mirror/emapa.owl $(MAPPINGDIR)/import-corrections.sssom.tsv | all_robot_plugins\n359: \t$(ROBOT) sssom:rename -i $< --sssom $(MAPPINGDIR)/import-corrections.sssom.tsv \\\n360: \t\t remove --base-iri $(URIBASE)/EMAPA_ --axioms external \\\n361: \t\t        --preserve-structure false --trim false \\\n362: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n363: \n364: imports/local-ma.owl: mirror/ma.owl $(MAPPINGDIR)/import-corrections.sssom.tsv | all_robot_plugins\n365: \t$(ROBOT) sssom:rename -i $< --sssom $(MAPPINGDIR)/import-corrections.sssom.tsv \\\n366: \t\t remove --base-iri $(URIBASE)/MA_ --axioms external \\\n367: \t\t        --preserve-structure false --trim false \\\n368: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n369: \n370: imports/local-xao.owl: mirror/xao.owl $(MAPPINGDIR)/import-corrections.sssom.tsv | all_robot_plugins\n371: \t$(ROBOT) sssom:rename -i $< --sssom $(MAPPINGDIR)/import-corrections.sssom.tsv \\\n372: \t\t remove --base-iri $(URIBASE)/XAO_ --axioms external \\\n373: \t\t        --preserve-structure false --trim false \\\n374: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n375: \n376: # And for those ones, we also remove the imports. They were last\n377: # refreshed in 2016, we don't want to bring in old issues from old\n378: # versions of Uberon, CL, RO, etc.\n379: # ----------------------------------------\n380: imports/local-poro.owl: mirror/poro.owl\n381: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< --select imports --trim false \\\n382: \t\t remove --base-iri $(URIBASE)/PORO_ --axioms external \\\n383: \t\t        --preserve-structure false --trim false \\\n384: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n385: \n386: imports/local-cteno.owl: mirror/cteno.owl\n387: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< --select imports --trim false \\\n388: \t\t remove --base-iri $(URIBASE)/CTENO_ --axioms external \\\n389: \t\t        --preserve-structure false --trim false \\\n390: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n391: \n392: imports/local-ceph.owl: mirror/ceph.owl\n393: \t$(ROBOT) remove -i $< --select imports --trim false \\\n394: \t\t remove --base-iri $(URIBASE)/CEPH_ --axioms external \\\n395: \t\t        --preserve-structure false --trim false \\\n396: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n397: \n398: \n399: # Allow quickly refreshing all \"local\" imports\n400: LOCAL_IMPORTS = ceph cl cteno ehdaa2 emapa fbbt fbdv ma poro sslso wbbt wbls xao zfa \\\n401: \t\tallen-hba allen-dhba allen-mba allen-dmba allen-pba\n402: all_local_imports: $(foreach imp,$(LOCAL_IMPORTS),$(IMPORTDIR)/local-$(imp).owl)\n403: \n404: else # IMP=false\n405: all_local_imports:\n406: \n407: endif\n408: \n409: # ----------------------------------------\n410: # EXTRACT ORCIDs INDIVIDUALS\n411: # ----------------------------------------\n412: \n413: # Extract ORCID from dcterms:contributor annotations\n414: $(IMPORTDIR)/orcidio_terms_combined.txt: $(SRC)\n415: \t$(ROBOT) query -f csv -i $< --query ../sparql/orcids.sparql $@.tmp &&\\\n416: \tcat $@.tmp | sort | uniq >  $@\n417: \n418: # Create orcidio_import.owl to extract individuals excluded in the merged_import.owl\n419: $(IMPORTDIR)/orcidio_import.owl: $(MIRRORDIR)/orcidio.owl $(IMPORTDIR)/orcidio_terms_combined.txt\n420: \tif [ $(IMP) = true ]; then $(ROBOT) filter -i $< -T $(IMPORTDIR)/orcidio_terms_combined.txt --trim false \\\n421: \t$(ANNOTATE_CONVERT_FILE); fi\n422: \n423: \n424: # ----------------------------------------\n425: # UNRELEASED PRODUCTS\n426: # ----------------------------------------\n427: \n428: # This section is intended to regroup rules that create files that are\n429: # not generated during a normal pipeline and that are never released,\n430: # but that someone may want to explicitly generate locally. This does\n431: # not include unreleased *reports* and *views/subsets*.\n432: \n433: # Markdown export\n434: markdown:\n435: \t$(OWLTOOLS) uberon.owl --merge-imports-closure --ontology-to-markdown md\n436: \n437: \n438: # nh-%: Composite product with no \"homology\" relation\n439: # ----------------------------------------\n440: nh-%.obo: composite-%.obo\n441: \tegrep -v 'relationship: (homologous_to|evolved_from)' $< > $@\n442: \n443: nh-%.owl: mh-%.obo\n444: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $< --check false -f obo -o $@\n445: \n446: \n447: # Extract taxon constraints (experimental, for propagation to GO?)\n448: # ----------------------------------------\n449: $(TMPDIR)/uberon-taxon-constraints.obo: $(SRC)\n450: \t$(SCRIPTSDIR)/obo-filter-relationships.pl -t only_in_taxon -t never_in_taxon $<  | \\\n451: \t\t$(SCRIPTSDIR)/obo-filter-tags.pl -t id -t name -t relationship - | \\\n452: \t\t$(SCRIPTSDIR)/obo-grep.pl --noheader -r relationship: - > $@.tmp && \\\n453: \t\tcat $@.tmp $(COMPONENTSDIR)/taxon_relations.obo > $@\n454: \n455: $(TMPDIR)/uberon-taxon-constraints.owl: $(TMPDIR)/uberon-taxon-constraints.obo\n456: \t$(ROBOT) expand --input $< -o $@\n457: \n458: \n459: # %-xf: Product without \"non-subclass cross-references\"?\n460: %-xf.obo: %.obo\n461: \tegrep -v '^xref: (OpenCyc|http)' $< > $@\n462: \n463: \n464: # %-noext: Product with only UBERON terms\n465: # (if you need this, consider using uberon-base instead)\n466: %-noext.obo: %.obo\n467: \t$(SCRIPTSDIR)/obo-grep.pl -r 'id: UBERON:' $< > $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n468: \n469: \n470: # %-names: Complete list of all term names in a product\n471: %-names.txt: %.obo\n472: \tgrep ^name: $< | grep -v obsolete | perl -npe 's@name: @@' > $@.tmp && sort -u $@.tmp > $@\n473: \n474: \n475: # ----------------------------------------\n476: # REPORTS\n477: # ----------------------------------------\n478: \n479: # This section regroup all rules that create reports. Not all of those\n480: # reports are released, and not all are automatically generated as part\n481: # of the normal pipeline.\n482: \n483: # Reports of closest inferred parent through object properties.\n484: # For an object property REL, such a report gives for every class C the\n485: # closest class P such as \"C is_a REL some P\" holds.\n486: # ----------------------------------------\n487: \n488: RPT_TAXA_ARGS =\n489: RPT_STAGE_RELS = RO:0002496 RO:0002497\n490: \n491: reports/%-part-of-parents.tsv: %.owl\n492: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner elk --reasoner mexr --log-error  --export-parents -p BFO:0000050 $(RPT_TAXA_ARGS) -o $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n493: .PRECIOUS: reports/%-part-of-parents.tsv\n494: \n495: reports/%-has-part-parents.tsv: %.owl\n496: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner elk --reasoner mexr --log-error  --export-parents -p BFO:0000051 $(RPT_TAXA_ARGS) -o $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n497: .PRECIOUS: reports/%-has-part-parents.tsv\n498: \n499: reports/%-dev-parents.tsv: %.owl\n500: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner elk --reasoner mexr --export-parents -p RO:0002202 RO:0002494 -o $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n501: .PRECIOUS: reports/%-dev-parents.tsv\n502: \n503: reports/%-tax-parents.tsv: %.owl\n504: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner elk --reasoner mexr --export-parents -p RO:0002162 -o $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n505: .PRECIOUS: reports/%-tax-parents.tsv\n506: \n507: reports/%-stage-parents.tsv: %.owl\n508: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner elk --reasoner mexr --log-error --export-parents -p $(RPT_STAGE_RELS) $(RPT_TAXA_ARGS) -o $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n509: .PRECIOUS: reports/%-stage-parents.tsv\n510: \n511: reports/%-function-parents.tsv: %.owl\n512: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner elk --reasoner mexr --export-parents -p RO:0002328 -o $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n513: .PRECIOUS: reports/%-function-parents.tsv\n514: \n515: # Similar to %-stage-parent above, but limited to a view\n516: reports/stages-%-report.tsv: subsets/%-view.owl\n517: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $<  --reasoner mexr --export-parents -p $(RPT_STAGE_RELS) -o $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n518: \n519: # Similar to %-part-of-parents above, but limited to a view\n520: reports/part-%-report.tsv: subsets/%-view.owl\n521: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner mexr --export-parents -p BFO:0000050 -o $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n522: \n523: \n524: # Generate the two reports above for a set of views\n525: # ----------------------------------------\n526: RPT_SPECIES = human mouse xenopus metazoan\n527: \n528: reports/stages: $(patsubst %,reports/stages-%-report.tsv,$(RPT_SPECIES))\n529: \n530: reports/parts: $(patsubst %,reports/part-%-report.tsv,$(RPT_SPECIES))\n531: \n532: \n533: # Various reports obtained by applying a SPARQL query\n534: # ----------------------------------------\n535: reports/uberon-%.csv: uberon.owl ../sparql/%.sparql\n536: \t$(ROBOT) query -i $< --query ../sparql/$*.sparql  $@.tmp && $(SCRIPTSDIR)/curiefy-purls.pl $@.tmp > $@ && rm $@.tmp\n537: \n538: # Same, but for the (preprocessed) -edit file rather than the main product\n539: reports/uberon-edit-%.csv: $(OWLSRC) ../sparql/%.sparql\n540: \t$(ROBOT) query -i $< --query ../sparql/$*.sparql  $@.tmp && $(SCRIPTSDIR)/curiefy-purls.pl $@.tmp > $@ && rm $@.tmp\n541: \n542: # Same as the first rule above, but IDs are not CURIEfied\n543: reports/%.csv: ../sparql/%.sparql uberon.owl\n544: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< query -s $< $@ -f csv\n545: \n546: \n547: # OBO checks (checks that requires an input file in OBO format)\n548: # ----------------------------------------\n549: %.obo-allchecks: $(REPORTDIR)/%.obo-OWL-check $(REPORTDIR)/%.obo-gocheck $(REPORTDIR)/%.obo-iconv\n550: \n551: # Check that an OBO-formatted product can be parsed back by the OWL API\n552: $(REPORTDIR)/%.obo-OWL-check: %.obo\n553: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $<\n554: \n555: # Check for non UTF-8 characters\n556: $(REPORTDIR)/%-iconv: %\n557: \ticonv -f UTF-8 -t UTF-8 $< > $@\n558: \n559: # Run a subset of the syntax and structure checks used by GO\n560: DISABLED_GO_CHECKS = multiply-labeled-edge \\\n561: \t\t     valid-id-space \\\n562: \t\t     isa-incomplete \\\n563: \t\t     ascii-check \\\n564: \t\t     has-definition \\\n565: \t\t     bad-pmid \\\n566: \t\t     ontology-declaration-check \\\n567: \t\t     referenced-id-syntax-check \\\n568: \t\t     owl-axiom-check \\\n569: \t\t     is-symmetric-check \\\n570: \t\t     xrf-abbs-check\n571: $(REPORTDIR)/%.obo-gocheck: %.obo | $(SCRIPTSDIR)/check-obo-for-standard-release.pl\n572: \t$(SCRIPTSDIR)/check-obo-for-standard-release.pl \\\n573: \t\t$(patsubst %,--disable-%,$(DISABLED_GO_CHECKS)) $< > $@.tmp && mv $@.tmp $@\n574: \n575: # Check for orphans\n576: $(REPORTDIR)/%-orphans: %.obo\n577: \t$(SCRIPTSDIR)/obo-grep.pl --neg -r \"(is_a|intersection_of|is_obsolete):\" $< | \\\n578: \t\t$(SCRIPTSDIR)/obo-grep.pl -r Term - | \\\n579: \t\t$(SCRIPTSDIR)/obo-grep.pl --neg -r \"id: UBERON:(0001062|0000000)\" - | \\\n580: \t\t$(SCRIPTSDIR)/obo-grep.pl -r Term - > $@.tmp && \\\n581: \t\t(egrep '^(id|name):'  $@.tmp > $@ || echo ok)\n582: \n583: # Syntactick check on intersection_of definitions\n584: $(REPORTDIR)/%-xp-check: %.obo\n585: \t$(SCRIPTSDIR)/obo-check-xps.pl $< > $@ 2> $@.err || (echo \"problems\" && exit 1)\n586: \n587: # Check for use of obsoleted terms\n588: $(REPORTDIR)/%-obscheck.txt: %.obo\n589: \t(($(SCRIPTSDIR)/obo-map-ids.pl --ignore-self-refs --use-consider --use-replaced_by $< $<) > /dev/null) 2>&1 > $@\n590: \n591: .PHONY: obocheck\n592: obocheck:\n593: \tfastobo-validator uberon-edit.obo\n594: \n595: .PHONY: test_obo_serialisation\n596: test_obo_serialisation:\n597: \t$(ROBOT) convert -i $(SRC) -f obo -o $(TMPDIR)/uberon_make_sure_serialisable_as_obo.obo\n598: \n599: .PHONY: test_obsolete\n600: test_obsolete:\n601: \t! grep \"! obsolete\" uberon-edit.obo\n602: \n603: .PHONY: test_owlaxioms\n604: test_owlaxioms:\n605: \t! grep \"owl-axioms: \" uberon-edit.obo\n606: \n607: \n608: # Cycle detection checks\n609: # ----------------------------------------\n610: \n611: $(REPORTDIR)/%-cycles: %.obo\n612: \t$(OWLTOOLS) --no-debug $< --list-cycles -f > $@\n613: \n614: src-cycles:\n615: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $(SRC) --list-cycles -f $(TMPDIR)/testcycles.tmp\n616: \n617: $(REPORTDIR)/%-allcycles: %.owl\n618: \t$(OWLTOOLS) --no-debug $< --list-cycles -f > $@\n619: \n620: \n621: # Other checks\n622: # ----------------------------------------\n623: \n624: # List of terms cross-referenced to one of Uberon's \"life cycle\" terms\n625: $(REPORTDIR)/life-cycle-xrefs.txt: $(SPARQLDIR)/life-cycle-xrefs.sparql $(SRC)\n626: \t$(ROBOT) reason -i $(SRC) query --use-graphs true --query $< $@.tmp.tsv\n627: \tsed -e '/?xref/d' -e 's/\"//g' <$@.tmp.tsv >$@ && rm $@.tmp.tsv\n628: \n629: # Disjoint violations\n630: $(REPORTDIR)/%-dv.txt: %.owl\n631: \t$(OWLTOOLS) --no-debug $<  $(QELK) --run-reasoner -r elk -u > $@.tmp && grep UNSAT $@.tmp > $@\n632: \n633: \n634: # ----------------------------------------\n635: # BRIDGE CHECKS\n636: # ----------------------------------------\n637: \n638: # Overall \"all-bridge\" check\n639: # ----------------------------------------\n640: \n641: # All the checks below need the taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl,\n642: # which should have been downloaded into mirror/ncbitaxondisjoints.owl\n643: # by the standard ODK import pipeline. So ideally, all the checks below\n644: # should just have to depend on mirror/ncbitaxondisjoints.owl. But the\n645: # QC checks are run under MIR=false IMP=false, so while the rule would\n646: # be invoked by Make it would not result in the mirror being downloaded\n647: # if it is not already available.\n648: # So instead, we make the checks depend on another file, and here we\n649: # 1. force the download of the mirror if it is not already there;\n650: # 2. create a link to that mirror.\n651: $(TMPDIR)/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl:\n652: \tif [ ! -f $(MIRRORDIR)/ncbitaxondisjoints.owl ]; then \\\n653: \t\t$(MAKE) $(MIRRORDIR)/ncbitaxondisjoints.owl MIR=true IMP=true ; \\\n654: \tfi && \\\n655: \tln -f -s ../$(MIRRORDIR)/ncbitaxondisjoints.owl $@\n656: \n657: # We create a merged ontology consisting of\n658: # (1) Uberon itself;\n659: # (2) the external-disjoints component;\n660: # (3) the taxslim including inter-taxon disjointness axioms;\n661: # (4) all the bridges to Uberon (except the EMAP bridge, which should\n662: #     probably be removed entirely from the repo anyway);\n663: # and we expand RO:0002175 (which was left unexpanded at the\n664: # preprocessing step, as it is only required for this check).\n665: # This can be used to reveal both internal inconsistencies within\n666: # Uberon, and the improper linking of a species AO class to an Uberon\n667: # class with a taxon constraints.\n668: ALL_UBERON_BRIDGES=$(shell ls $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-*.owl | grep -v emap.owl)\n669: $(TMPDIR)/uberon-edit-plus-tax-equivs.owl: $(OWLSRC) \\\n670: \t\t\t\t\t   $(COMPONENTSDIR)/external-disjoints.obo \\\n671: \t\t\t\t\t   $(TMPDIR)/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl \\\n672: \t\t\t\t\t   $(TMPDIR)/bridges\n673: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< -i $(COMPONENTSDIR)/external-disjoints.obo \\\n674: \t\t       -i $(TMPDIR)/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl \\\n675: \t\t       $(foreach bridge, $(ALL_UBERON_BRIDGES), -i $(bridge)) \\\n676: \t\t expand \\\n677: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n678: .PRECIOUS: $(TMPDIR)/uberon-edit-plus-tax-equivs.owl\n679: \n680: $(REPORTDIR)/taxon-constraint-check.txt: $(TMPDIR)/uberon-edit-plus-tax-equivs.owl\n681: \t$(ROBOT) reason -i $< -r ELK > $@\n682: \n683: \n684: # Individual bridge checks\n685: # ----------------------------------------\n686: \n687: # There are three flavours of bridge checks (see below). Here we define\n688: # whhich bridges are subjected to which checks.\n689: EXTRA_FULL_CHECK_AO_LIST = caro\n690: CHECK_AO_LIST = $(EXTRA_FULL_CHECK_AO_LIST) wbls wbbt\n691: QUICK_CHECK_AO_LIST = $(CHECK_AO_LIST) fbbt zfa xao fma ma emapa bfo\n692: \n693: quick-bridge-checks: $(foreach ao, $(QUICK_CHECK_AO_LIST), $(REPORTDIR)/quick-bridge-check-$(ao).txt)\n694: bridge-checks: $(foreach ao, $(CHECK_AO_LIST), $(REPORTDIR)/bridge-check-$(ao).txt)\n695: extra-full-bridge-checks: $(foreach ao, $(EXTRA_FULL_CHECK_AO_LIST), $(REPORTDIR)/extra-full-bridge-check-$(ao).txt)\n696: \n697: \n698: # A quick bridge check uses only uberon plus taxon constraints plus\n699: # bridging axioms, *not* the axioms in the source ontology itself.\n700: $(REPORTDIR)/quick-bridge-check-%.txt: $(POSTPROCESS_SRC) \\\n701: \t\t\t\t       $(COMPONENTSDIR)/external-disjoints.obo \\\n702: \t\t\t\t       $(TMPDIR)/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl \\\n703: \t\t\t\t       $(TMPDIR)/bridges\n704: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< -i $(COMPONENTSDIR)/external-disjoints.obo \\\n705: \t\t       -i $(TMPDIR)/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl \\\n706: \t\t       -i $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-$*.owl \\\n707: \t\t reason -r ELK > $@\n708: \n709: \n710: # A (standard) bridge check uses uberon, the taxon constraints, the\n711: # bridge itself, and the corresponding external ontology.\n712: # For this check, we separate the production of the merged ontology\n713: # from the production of the report.\n714: # 1. The merge\n715: $(REPORTDIR)/bridge-check-%.owl: $(POSTPROCESS_SRC) \\\n716: \t\t\t\t $(COMPONENTSDIR)/external-disjoints.obo \\\n717: \t\t\t\t $(TMPDIR)/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl \\\n718: \t\t\t\t $(TMPDIR)/bridges \\\n719: \t\t\t\t $(IMPORTDIR)/local-%.owl\n720: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< -i $(COMPONENTSDIR)/external-disjoints.obo \\\n721: \t\t       -i $(TMPDIR)/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl \\\n722: \t\t       -i $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-$*.owl \\\n723: \t\t       -i $(IMPORTDIR)/local-$*.owl \\\n724: \t\t convert -f ofn -o $@\n725: .PRECIOUS: $(REPORTDIR)/bridge-check-%.owl\n726: \n727: # 2. The reasoner's report (this is the actual check)\n728: $(REPORTDIR)/bridge-check-%.txt: $(REPORTDIR)/bridge-check-%.owl\n729: \t$(ROBOT) reason -i $< -r ELK > $@\n730: \n731: # 3. The reasoner's explanations for any unsats\n732: # (only generated on request, not part of the check)\n733: $(REPORTDIR)/expl-bridge-check-%.txt: $(REPORTDIR)/bridge-check-%.owl\n734: \t$(ROBOT) explain -i $< -M unsatisfiability -u all -r ELK -e $@\n735: \n736: \n737: # An extra-full bridge check is the same as a standard bridge check, but\n738: # includes pending disjoints. This is a very strict check and we don't\n739: # expect it to pass for lots of taxon-specific ontologies.\n740: $(REPORTDIR)/extra-full-bridge-check-%.txt: $(REPORTDIR)/bridge-check-%.owl $(COMPONENTSDIR)/pending-disjoints.obo\n741: \t$(ROBOT) merge $(foreach prereq, $^, -i $(prereq)) \\\n742: \t\t reason -r ELK > $@\n743: \n744: \n745: # BFO bridge checks\n746: # ----------------------------------------\n747: # BFO needs special treatment because we don't have a \"local-bfo.owl\" or\n748: # a \"local-ro.owl\" mirror as we do for the taxons-specific ontologies;\n749: # and since these checks are typically run with MIR=false, they would\n750: # fail using the rules above because mirror/bfo.owl and mirror/ro.owl\n751: # would be nowhere to be found. So here we load these external\n752: # ontologies from their online locations.\n753: \n754: $(REPORTDIR)/bfo-check.txt: $(OWLSRC) $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-bfo.owl\n755: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< -i $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-bfo.owl \\\n756: \t\t       -I $(URIBASE)/bfo.owl -I $(URIBASE)/ro.owl \\\n757: \t\t reason -r ELK --equivalent-classes-allowed asserted-only > $@\n758: \n759: # Similar to above, but with the basic product and without RO\n760: $(REPORTDIR)/bfo-basic-check.txt: uberon-basic.owl $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-bfo.owl\n761: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< -i $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-bfo.owl \\\n762: \t\t       -I $(URIBASE)/bfo.owl \\\n763: \t\t reason -r ELK > $@\n764: \n765: \n766: # ----------------------------------------\n767: # SUBSETS & VIEWS\n768: # ----------------------------------------\n769: \n770: # Create a seed from the standard (ODK-generated) Uberon seed to which\n771: # we add CL terms. This seed is used by several subsets below.\n772: tmp/simple-slim-seed.txt: $(SRCMERGED) $(SIMPLESEED)\n773: \t$(ROBOT) query -f csv -i $< --query ../sparql/cl_terms.sparql $@.tmp && \\\n774: \tcat $@.tmp $(SIMPLESEED) | sort | uniq >  $@\n775: \n776: \n777: # System-specific subsets\n778: # ----------------------------------------\n779: \n780: TERM_nephron := UBERON:0001285\n781: TERM_musculoskeletal := UBERON:0002204\n782: TERM_excretory := UBERON:0001008\n783: TERM_reproductive := UBERON:0000990\n784: TERM_digestive := UBERON:0001007\n785: TERM_nervous := UBERON:0001016\n786: TERM_sensory := UBERON:0004456\n787: TERM_immune := UBERON:0002405\n788: TERM_circulatory := UBERON:0001009\n789: TERM_pulmonary := UBERON:0001004\n790: TERM_cranial := UBERON:0010323\n791: TERM_renal := UBERON:0001008\n792: TERM_appendicular := UBERON:0002091\n793: TERM_life_cycle_stage := UBERON:0000105\n794: \n795: # Subset generation command\n796: SUBSETCMD=$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner-query -r elk -d  \"$(PART_OF) some $(TERM_ID)\" --reasoner-query $(TERM_ID) --make-ontology-from-results $(URIBASE)/uberon/$@ -o $@  2>&1 > $@.LOG\n797: \n798: # Source file for all the subsets generated below\n799: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl: uberon.owl\n800: \t$(ROBOT) remove --input $< --axioms \"equivalent disjoint type abox\" \\\n801: \t\t remove --exclude-term BFO:0000050 --select \"object-properties\" \\\n802: \t\t        -o $@\n803: .PRECIOUS: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n804: \n805: subsets/appendicular-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n806: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_appendicular))\n807: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n808: \n809: subsets/circulatory-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n810: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_circulatory))\n811: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n812: \n813: subsets/cranial-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n814: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_cranial))\n815: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n816: \n817: subsets/digestive-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n818: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_digestive))\n819: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n820: \n821: subsets/excretory-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n822: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_excretory))\n823: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n824: \n825: subsets/immune-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n826: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_immune))\n827: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n828: \n829: subsets/musculoskeletal-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n830: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_musculoskeletal))\n831: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n832: \n833: subsets/nephron-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n834: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_nephron))\n835: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n836: \n837: subsets/nervous-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n838: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_nervous))\n839: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n840: \n841: subsets/pulmonary-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n842: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_pulmonary))\n843: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n844: \n845: subsets/renal-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n846: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_renal))\n847: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n848: \n849: subsets/reproductive-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n850: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_reproductive))\n851: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n852: \n853: subsets/sensory-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n854: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_sensory))\n855: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n856: \n857: subsets/life-stages-minimal.owl: subsets/merged-partonomy.owl\n858: \t$(eval TERM_ID := $(TERM_life_cycle_stage))\n859: \t$(SUBSETCMD)\n860: \n861: # TODO: need to add subclass axioms for all intersections\n862: subsets/musculoskeletal-full.obo: uberon.owl\n863: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner-query -r elk -d -c $(URIBASE)/uberon/$@ \\\n864: \t\t    \"$(PART_OF) some UBERON_0002204\" \\\n865: \t\t    -o -f obo file://`pwd`/$@  --reasoner-dispose\n866: \n867: subsets/vertebrate-head.obo: composite-vertebrate.owl\n868: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner-query -r elk -d \"$(PART_OF) some UBERON_0000033\" \\\n869: \t\t    --make-ontology-from-results $(URIBASE)/uberon/$@ \\\n870: \t\t    -o -f obo --no-check $@ --reasoner-dispose 2>&1 > $@.LOG\n871: \n872: \n873: # Life stages subsets\n874: # ----------------------------------------\n875: \n876: # TODO - switch to purls for OWL once released\n877: subsets/life-stages-mammal.owl: subsets/life-stages-core.owl $(TMPDIR)/mmusdv.owl $(TMPDIR)/hsapdv.owl\n878: \t$(ROBOT) merge $(foreach input, $^, -i $(input)) -o $@\n879: \n880: subsets/life-stages-composite.owl: composite-metazoan.owl\n881: \t$(ROBOT) query --input $< \\\n882: \t\t       --update $(SPARQLDIR)/inject-life-stages-subset.ru \\\n883: \t\t       --update $(SPARQLDIR)/inject-subset-declaration.ru \\\n884: \t\t       --output $@.tmp.owl && mv $@.tmp.owl $@ &&\\\n885: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $@ --extract-ontology-subset --fill-gaps --subset life_stage \\\n886: \t\t       -o $@.tmp.owl && mv $@.tmp.owl $@ && \\\n887: \t$(ROBOT) annotate --input $@ --ontology-iri $(ONTBASE)/$@ $(ANNOTATE_ONTOLOGY_VERSION) \\\n888: \t\t          -o $@.tmp.owl && mv $@.tmp.owl $@\n889: \n890: subsets/life-stages-core.obo: uberon.owl\n891: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner-query -r elk -l 'life cycle stage' \\\n892: \t\t    --make-ontology-from-results $(URIBASE)/uberon/$@ \\\n893: \t\t    --add-ontology-annotation $(DC)/description \"Life cycle stage subset of uberon core (generic stages only)\" \\\n894: \t\t    -o -f obo $@ --reasoner-dispose 2>&1 > $@.LOG\n895: \n896: subsets/life-stages-core.owl: uberon.owl\n897: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner-query -r elk -l 'life cycle stage' \\\n898: \t\t    --make-ontology-from-results $(URIBASE)/uberon/$@ \\\n899: \t\t    --add-ontology-annotation $(DC)/description \"Life cycle stage subset of uberon core (generic stages only)\" \\\n900: \t\t    -o file://`pwd`/$@ --reasoner-dispose 2>&1 > $@.LOG\n901: \n902: \n903: # Taxon subsets\n904: # ----------------------------------------\n905: \n906: TAXON_ID_human            = NCBITaxon:9606\n907: TAXON_ID_mouse            = NCBITaxon:10090\n908: TAXON_ID_xenopus          = NCBITaxon:8353\n909: TAXON_ID_drosophila       = NCBITaxon:7227\n910: TAXON_ID_gnathostome      = NCBITaxon:7776\n911: TAXON_ID_amniote          = NCBITaxon:32524\n912: TAXON_ID_euarchontoglires = NCBITaxon:314146\n913: TAXON_ID_nematode         = NCBITaxon:6237\n914: TAXON_ID_zebrafish        = NCBITaxon:7955\n915: \n916: # Strategy to use to create the taxon subsets:\n917: # - default: OWLTools' original strategy; given a root class R and a\n918: #            taxon T, assert 'R SubClassOf: in_taxon some T' and exclude\n919: #            all classes that are unsatisfiable because of that\n920: #            assertion.\n921: # - precise: alternative strategy; given a root class R and a taxon T,\n922: #            iterate through all subclasses C of R and include classes\n923: #            for which the expression 'C and in_taxon some T' is\n924: #            satisfiable; about 3-5 times slower than 'default'.\n925: TAXON_SUBSET_STRATEGY = default\n926: \n927: TAXON_SUBSET_ROOTS = UBERON:0001062 UBERON:0000000\n928: \n929: # Create a taxon-specific subset. This rule creates two distinct files:\n930: # (1) the subset proper (subsets/%-view.owl), which can be used on its\n931: #     own (and can be published as a release artifact if desired);\n932: # (2) a small file containing oboInOwl:inSubset annotations to \"tag\" all\n933: #     terms that belong to the subset (subsets/%-tags.ofn); that file\n934: #     can then be merged to the main release product (last step of the\n935: #     \"BUILDING UBERON ITSELF\" pipeline).\n936: .PRECIOUS: subsets/%-view.owl\n937: subsets/%-view.owl subsets/%-tags.ofn: $(POSTPROCESS_SRC) | all_robot_plugins\n938: \t$(ROBOT) uberon:create-species-subset --input $< \\\n939: \t\t                              --taxon $(TAXON_ID_$*) \\\n940: \t\t                              --strategy $(TAXON_SUBSET_STRATEGY) \\\n941: \t\t                              --reasoner ELK \\\n942: \t\t                              $(foreach root,$(TAXON_SUBSET_ROOTS),--root $(root)) \\\n943: \t\t                              --prefix 'uberon: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon/core#' \\\n944: \t\t                              --subset-name uberon:$*_subset \\\n945: \t\t                              --only-tag-in UBERON: \\\n946: \t\t                              --write-tags-to subsets/$*-tags.ofn \\\n947: \t\t reason --reasoner ELK --equivalent-classes-allowed all \\\n948: \t\t        --exclude-tautologies structural \\\n949: \t\t relax \\\n950: \t\t remove --axioms equivalent \\\n951: \t\t relax \\\n952: \t\t reduce --reasoner ELK \\\n953: \t\t annotate --ontology-iri $(ONTBASE)/subsets/$*-view.owl \\\n954: \t\t          --version-iri $(ONTBASE)/releases/$(VERSION)/subsets/$*-view.owl \\\n955: \t\t          --annotation owl:versionInfo $(VERSION) \\\n956: \t\t convert --format ofn --output subsets/$*-view.owl\n957: \n958: \n959: # Other subsets\n960: # ----------------------------------------\n961: \n962: # Cumbo subset\n963: subsets/cumbo.owl: uberon-basic.owl\n964: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --extract-ontology-subset --subset cumbo --iri $(URIBASE)/uberon/$@ -o $@\n965: \n966: # Common anatony subset\n967: common-anatomy.owl: $(ONT).owl\n968: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --extract-ontology-subset --fill-gaps --subset common_anatomy \\\n969: \t\t    -o $@.tmp.owl && mv $@.tmp.owl $@ && \\\n970: \t$(ROBOT) annotate --input $@ --ontology-iri $(ONTBASE)/$@ $(ANNOTATE_ONTOLOGY_VERSION) \\\n971: \t\t          -o $@.tmp.owl && mv $@.tmp.owl $@\n972: .PRECIOUS: common-anatomy.owl\n973: \n974: subsets/immaterial.obo: uberon.owl\n975: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --reasoner-query -r elk -d  UBERON_0000466 \\\n976: \t\t    --make-ontology-from-results $(URIBASE)/uberon/$@ \\\n977: \t\t    -o -f obo $@ --reasoner-dispose 2>&1 > $@.LOG\n978: \n979: %-partview.owl: %.owl\n980: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --remove-subset grouping_class --remove-subset upper_level \\\n981: \t\t    --bpvo --reflexive --prefix \"\" --suffix \" part\" -r elk -p BFO:0000050 --replace \\\n982: \t\t    --set-ontology-id $(URIBASE)/uberon/$@ -o -f ttl $@\n983: \n984: %-exprview.owl: %.owl\n985: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< $(URIBASE)/ro.owl --merge-support-ontologies \\\n986: \t\t--remove-subset grouping_class --remove-subset upper_level \\\n987: \t\t--bpvo --prefix \" expressed in\" --suffix \"\" -r elk -p BFO:0000050 --replace \\\n988: \t\t--set-ontology-id $(URIBASE)/uberon/$@ -o -f ttl $@\n989: \n990: %-homolview.owl: %.owl\n991: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< $(URIBASE)/ro.owl homologous-to-part-of.obo --merge-support-ontologies \\\n992: \t\t--remove-subset grouping_class --remove-subset upper_level \\\n993: \t\t--bpvo --prefix \" expressed in\" --suffix \"\" -r elk -p UBREL:0002000 --replace \\\n994: \t\t--set-ontology-id $(URIBASE)/uberon/$@ -o -f ttl $@\n995: \n996: \n997: # ----------------------------------------\n998: # COMPOSITE ANATOMY\n999: # ----------------------------------------\n1000: \n1001: # Source files for the collected/composite ontologies\n1002: # ----------------------------------------\n1003: COLLECTED_drosophila_SOURCES =       $(IMPORTDIR)/local-fbbt.owl \\\n1004: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-fbdv.owl \\\n1005: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-fbbt.owl \\\n1006: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-fbdv.owl \\\n1007: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/cl-bridge-to-fbbt.owl\n1008: \n1009: COLLECTED_worm_SOURCES =             $(IMPORTDIR)/local-wbbt.owl \\\n1010: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-wbls.owl \\\n1011: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-wbbt.owl \\\n1012: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-wbls.owl \\\n1013: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/cl-bridge-to-wbbt.owl\n1014: \n1015: COLLECTED_zebrafish_SOURCES =        $(IMPORTDIR)/local-zfa.owl \\\n1016: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-zfa.owl \\\n1017: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/cl-bridge-to-zfa.owl\n1018: \n1019: COLLECTED_xenopus_SOURCES =          $(IMPORTDIR)/local-xao.owl \\\n1020: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-xao.owl \\\n1021: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/cl-bridge-to-xao.owl\n1022: \n1023: COLLECTED_human_SOURCES =            $(IMPORTDIR)/local-ehdaa2.owl \\\n1024: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-ehdaa2.owl \\\n1025: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-aeo.owl \\\n1026: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-hsapdv.owl \\\n1027: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/cl-bridge-to-ehdaa2.owl \\\n1028: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/cl-bridge-to-aeo.owl \\\n1029: \t\t\t\t     $(TMPDIR)/hsapdv.owl\n1030: \n1031: COLLECTED_mouse_SOURCES =            $(IMPORTDIR)/local-emapa.owl \\\n1032: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-emapa.owl \\\n1033: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-mmusdv.owl \\\n1034: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/cl-bridge-to-emapa.owl \\\n1035: \t\t\t\t     $(TMPDIR)/mmusdv.owl \\\n1036: \n1037: # In principle this should also include FMA and its bridges, but we have\n1038: # been excluded those for a while\n1039: COLLECTED_adult_mammal_SOURCES =     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-ma.owl \\\n1040: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-ma.owl \\\n1041: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/cl-bridge-to-ma.owl\n1042: \n1043: COLLECTED_embryonic_mammal_SOURCES = $(COLLECTED_human_SOURCES) \\\n1044: \t\t\t\t     $(COLLECTED_mouse_SOURCES)\n1045: \n1046: COLLECTED_mammal_SOURCES =           $(COLLECTED_adult_mammal_SOURCES) \\\n1047: \t\t\t\t     $(COLLECTED_embryonic_mammal_SOURCES) \\\n1048: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-allen-dhba.owl \\\n1049: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-allen-dmba.owl \\\n1050: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-allen-hba.owl \\\n1051: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-allen-mba.owl \\\n1052: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-allen-pba.owl \\\n1053: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-dhba.owl \\\n1054: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-dmba.owl \\\n1055: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-mba.owl \\\n1056: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-hba.owl \\\n1057: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-pba.owl\n1058: \n1059: COLLECTED_zfa_plus_mammal_SOURCES =  $(COLLECTED_mammal_SOURCES) \\\n1060: \t\t\t\t     $(COLLECTED_zebrafish_SOURCES)\n1061: \n1062: COLLECTED_anamniote_SOURCES =        $(COLLECTED_zebrafish_SOURCES) \\\n1063: \t\t\t\t     $(COLLECTED_xenopus_SOURCES)\n1064: \n1065: COLLECTED_amniote_SOURCES =          $(COLLECTED_mammal_SOURCES)\n1066: \n1067: COLLECTED_tetrapod_SOURCES =         $(COLLECTED_amniote_SOURCES) \\\n1068: \t\t\t\t     $(COLLECTED_xenopus_SOURCES)\n1069: \n1070: COLLECTED_vertebrate_SOURCES =       $(COLLECTED_tetrapod_SOURCES) \\\n1071: \t\t\t\t     $(COLLECTED_zebrafish_SOURCES)\n1072: \n1073: COLLECTED_metazoan_SOURCES =         $(COLLECTED_vertebrate_SOURCES) \\\n1074: \t\t\t\t     $(COLLECTED_drosophila_SOURCES) \\\n1075: \t\t\t\t     $(COLLECTED_worm_SOURCES) \\\n1076: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-sslso.owl \\\n1077: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-sslso.owl \\\n1078: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-ceph.owl \\\n1079: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-cteno.owl \\\n1080: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-poro.owl\n1081: \n1082: COLLECTED_lifestages_SOURCES =       $(SUBSETDIR)/life-stages-minimal.owl \\\n1083: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-fbdv.owl \\\n1084: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-wbls.owl \\\n1085: \t\t\t\t     $(IMPORTDIR)/local-sslso.owl \\\n1086: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-fbdv.owl \\\n1087: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-wbls.owl \\\n1088: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-mmusdv.owl \\\n1089: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-hsapdv.owl \\\n1090: \t\t\t\t     $(BRIDGEDIR)/uberon-bridge-to-sslso.owl \\\n1091: \t\t\t\t     $(TMPDIR)/xao-ls-bridged.owl\n1092: \n1093: \n1094: # Composite pipeline proper\n1095: # ----------------------------------------\n1096: \n1097: # Set to false to keep disjointness axioms in collected/composite\n1098: # products. Such axioms are stripped by default because too many\n1099: # taxon-specific ontologies are inconsistent with Uberon.\n1100: COMPOSITE_STRIP_DISJOINTS=true\n1101: ifeq ($(COMPOSITE_STRIP_DISJOINTS),true)\n1102: COMPOSITE_STRIPPING_COMMAND = remove --axioms \"DisjointClasses DisjointUnion\"\n1103: endif\n1104: \n1105: # Step 1: Create a \"collected\" ontology, which is simply a merge of\n1106: # Uberon, CL, and the components listed in the COLLECTED_*_SOURCES\n1107: # variables above.\n1108: .PRECIOUS: $(TMPDIR)/collected-%.owl\n1109: $(TMPDIR)/collected-%.owl: $(BRIDGEDIR)/collected-%-hdr.owl $(POSTPROCESS_SRC) $(IMPORTDIR)/local-cl.owl \\\n1110: \t\t $$(COLLECTED_$$*_SOURCES) $(TMPDIR)/bridges\n1111: \t$(ROBOT) merge $(foreach src,$^,-i $(src)) -o $@\n1112: \n1113: # Step 1b: collected-metazoan is not merely an intermediate towards\n1114: # composite-metazoan, it is also a released artefact.\n1115: collected-metazoan.owl: $(TMPDIR)/collected-metazoan.owl\n1116: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< $(COMPOSITE_STRIPPING_COMMAND) \\\n1117: \t\t annotate --ontology-iri $(ONTBASE)/$@ $(ANNOTATE_ONTOLOGY_VERSION) -o $@\n1118: \n1119: # Step 1c: collected-lifestages is special in that it should not\n1120: # include Uberon and CL (only the life-stages-minimal subset).\n1121: $(TMPDIR)/collected-lifestages.owl: $(BRIDGEDIR)/collected-lifestages-hdr.owl \\\n1122: \t\t\t\t    $(COLLECTED_lifestages_SOURCES)\n1123: \t$(ROBOT) merge $(foreach src,$^,-i $(src)) -o $@\n1124: \n1125: # Step 1d: And it is also a released artefact.\n1126: collected-lifestages.owl: $(TMPDIR)/collected-lifestages.owl\n1127: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< $(COMPOSITE_STRIPPING_COMMAND) \\\n1128: \t\t annotate --ontology-iri $(ONTBASE)/$@ $(ANNOTATE_ONTOLOGY_VERSION) -o $@\n1129: \n1130: # Step 2: Create a \"composite\" ontology. This is the core of the\n1131: # composite pipeline. It heavily relies on the Uberon plugin for ROBOT,\n1132: # which provides the 'merge-species' and 'merge-equivalent-sets'\n1133: # commands.\n1134: .PRECIOUS: $(TMPDIR)/composite-%.owl\n1135: $(TMPDIR)/composite-%.owl: $(TMPDIR)/collected-%.owl $(TMPDIR)/tax-merges.tsv | all_robot_plugins\n1136: \t$(ROBOT) merge -i $< $(COMPOSITE_STRIPPING_COMMAND) \\\n1137: \t\t uberon:merge-species --remove-declarations \\\n1138: \t\t                      --extended-translation \\\n1139: \t\t                      --translate-gcas \\\n1140: \t\t                      --batch-file $(TMPDIR)/tax-merges.tsv \\\n1141: \t\t uberon:merge-equivalent-sets -s UBERON=10 -s CL=9 -s CARO=5 \\\n1142: \t\t                              -l UBERON=10 -l CL=9 \\\n1143: \t\t                              -d UBERON=10 -d CL=9 \\\n1144: \t\t reason -r ELK --equivalent-classes-allowed all \\\n1145: \t\t relax \\\n1146: \t\t reduce -r ELK -o $@\n1147: \n1148: # Step 2a: The \"tax-merges.tsv\" file used in the rule above is automatically\n1149: # derived from the list of species in config/taxa.yaml.\n1150: $(TMPDIR)/tax-merges.tsv: $(SCRIPTSDIR)/taxa.py config/taxa.yaml\n1151: \tpython3 $(SCRIPTSDIR)/taxa.py make-merge-table config/taxa.yaml > $@\n1152: \n1153: # Step 3: Annotate the result of step 2. This is a separate step only so\n1154: # that we can have explicit rules for composite-metazoan, -vertebrate,\n1155: # and -lifestages, because the ODK-generated Makefile already defines a\n1156: # non-implicit rules with those targets.\n1157: composite-%.owl: $(TMPDIR)/composite-%.owl\n1158: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $< --ontology-iri $(ONTBASE)/$@ $(ANNOTATE_ONTOLOGY_VERSION) -o $@\n1159: composite-metazoan.owl: $(TMPDIR)/composite-metazoan.owl\n1160: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $< --ontology-iri $(ONTBASE)/$@ $(ANNOTATE_ONTOLOGY_VERSION) -o $@\n1161: composite-vertebrate.owl: $(TMPDIR)/composite-vertebrate.owl\n1162: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $< --ontology-iri $(ONTBASE)/$@ $(ANNOTATE_ONTOLOGY_VERSION) -o $@\n1163: composite-lifestages.owl: $(TMPDIR)/composite-lifestages.owl\n1164: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $< --ontology-iri $(ONTBASE)/$@ $(ANNOTATE_ONTOLOGY_VERSION) -o $@\n1165: \n1166: # XAO contains both anatomical terms and life stage terms. To build\n1167: # collected-lifestages (step 1c above), we need to extract the life stage\n1168: # terms only (all descendants of XAO:1000000, \"Xenopus developmental stage\"),\n1169: # and bridge them with corresponding Uberon terms.\n1170: $(TMPDIR)/xao-ls-bridged.owl: $(IMPORTDIR)/local-xao.owl \\\n1171: \t\t\t\t       $(MAPPINGDIR)/uberon-local.sssom.tsv \\\n1172: \t\t\t\t       | all_robot_plugins\n1173: \t$(ROBOT) extract -i $< --method MIREOT --branch-from-term XAO:1000000 \\\n1174: \t\t sssom:inject --sssom $(MAPPINGDIR)/uberon-local.sssom.tsv \\\n1175: \t\t              --ruleset $(BRIDGEDIR)/bridge-xao-ls.rules \\\n1176: \t\t              -o $@\n1177: \n1178: # SSLSO contains the entirety of HsapDv, but to construct collected-human,\n1179: # we specifically need the HsapDv terms only, so we extract them from SSLSO.\n1180: # This is also needed to construct the life-stages-mammal subset.\n1181: $(TMPDIR)/hsapdv.owl: $(IMPORTDIR)/local-sslso.owl\n1182: \t$(ROBOT) extract -i $< --method MIREOT --branch-from-term HsapDv:0000000 -o $@\n1183: \n1184: # Ditto for MmusDv.\n1185: $(TMPDIR)/mmusdv.owl: $(IMPORTDIR)/local-sslso.owl\n1186: \t$(ROBOT) extract -i $< --method MIREOT --branch-from-term MmusDv:0000000 -o $@\n1187: \n1188: \n1189: # Some special products derived from the products generated above\n1190: # ----------------------------------------\n1191: BASICRELS = BFO:0000050 RO:0002202 immediate_transformation_of transformation_of\n1192: \n1193: composite-metazoan-basic.owl: composite-metazoan.owl\n1194: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --extract-mingraph --remove-axiom-annotations \\\n1195: \t\t    --make-subset-by-properties -f $(BASICRELS) \\\n1196: \t\t    -o -f obo --no-check $@.tmp && \\\n1197: \tgrep -v '^owl-axioms:' $@.tmp > $@ && \\\n1198: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $@ --ontology-iri $(ONTBASE)/$@ $(ANNOTATE_ONTOLOGY_VERSION) \\\n1199: \t\t convert --check false -f owl -o $@.tmp && \\\n1200: \tmv $@.tmp $@\n1201: \n1202: composite-vertebrate-basic.owl: composite-vertebrate.owl\n1203: \t$(OWLTOOLS) $< --extract-mingraph --remove-axiom-annotations \\\n1204: \t\t    --make-subset-by-properties -f $(BASICRELS) \\\n1205: \t\t    -o -f obo --no-check $@.tmp && \\\n1206: \tgrep -v '^owl-axioms:' $@.tmp > $@ && \\\n1207: \t$(ROBOT) annotate -i $@ --ontology-iri $(ONTBASE)/$@ $(ANNOTATE_ONTOLOGY_VERSION) \\\n1208: \t\t convert --check false -f owl -o $@.tmp && \\\n1209: \tmv $@.tmp $@\n1210: \n1211: \n1212: # Helper commands for composite-* stuff\n1213: # ----------------------------------------\n1214: \n1215: # Create a diff with the latest released version\n1216: $(TMPDIR)/composite-metazoan-last-release.owl:\n1217: \twget https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/releases/latest/download/composite-metazoan.owl -O $@\n1218: \n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1218. Use offset=1219 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## Customize Makefile settings for uberon\n##\n## If you need to customize your Makefile, make\n## changes here rather than in the main Makefile\n\nBRIDGEDIR =            bridge\nCONFIGDIR =            config\nTAXMODSDIR =           taxmods\nBRI=                   true\n\nOWLSRC =               $(TMPDIR)/uberon-edit.owl\nPOSTPROCESS_SRC =      $(TMPDIR)/uberon.owl\nCATALOG_DYNAMIC =      catalog-dynamic.xml\nOWLTOOLS_NO_CAT=       OWLTOOLS_MEMORY=$(OWLTOOLS_MEMORY) owltools\nOWLTOOLS_CAT_DYNAMIC=  OWLTOOLS_MEMORY=$(OWLTOOLS_MEMORY) owltools --catalog-xml $(CATALOG_DYNAMIC)\n\n\nDC =                   http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1\nRELEASE =              $(URIBASE)/uberon/releases/$(TODAY)\nQELK =                 --silence-elk","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"src/ontology/uberon.Makefile","time":{"start":1778903945098,"end":1778903945113}},"id":"prt_e2ef00ef2001G7PeE6hspBHpS7","sessionID":"ses_1d1105b2dffeoypsZAOjVXoVJo","messageID":"msg_e2eefec24001Tq5xo1r3uW8RfQ"}}
